<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-22T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-22T17:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">671.116/49: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Rumania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Owsley</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-22T17:00:00-05:00">March 22, 1935—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2. Your 3, March 2, 4 p.m. Please telegraph whether suspension of
                                authorizations for importation of American merchandise still obtains
                                and date on which action was taken on the Department’s telegram No.
                                1 March 11, 5 p.m. Also report any information you may have as to
                                the Rumanian Government’s reaction to your note and as to when a
                                reply may be expected.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>